    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix get_current_time() function to handle clock_gettime errors\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_current_time()` function in both UE and GNB tracer applications was not properly handling errors from `clock_gettime()`. This could lead to undefined behavior when the function failed, as it would return uninitialized data. The fix adds proper error handling and initialization.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/t_tracer_app_ue.c`: Added error handling for `clock_gettime()` and initialized timespec structure\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/t_tracer_app_gnb.c`: Applied same fix for consistency\n- Both files: Added `#include <errno.h>` for error reporting\n\n### Reproduction\nIn rare cases where `clock_gettime(CLOCK_MONOTONIC, &time)` fails (e.g., due to system resource issues), the function would previously return uninitialized stack data. This could cause:\n- Incorrect timing calculations in trace recordings\n- Unpredictable behavior in time-based filtering\n- Potential segfaults if the garbage values were used in subsequent calculations\n\nThe issue is most likely to manifest under high system load or when system time functions are temporarily unavailable.\n\n"
}